{{see|woot}}
==English [[Leet]]==

===Pronunciation===
wo͞ot, /wuːt/, /wu:t/ 

===Interjection===
'''w00t'''!
# (''slang'') Used to express [[joy]], [[success]].

====Usage notes====
The term '''w00t''' is used to express happiness or excitement, usually over the Internet. The expression is most popular on [[Usenet]] posts, multiplayer computer games (especially [[first person shooter]]s), [[Internet relay chat|IRC]] chats, and [[instant messages]], though use on the [[World Wide Web]] is by no means uncommon.  There are many different theories as to how the term was concieved.  It can also stand for "what?" if a question mark is placed after it, as in "Wo0t?."

